New Features and Important Changes in GammaLib 00-04-07

Author(s) : Juergen Knoedlseder

February 24, 2011


1. Introduction
---------------
This document briefly summarizes module by module the most important changes
made since the last release of GammaLib.


2. Configuration
-----------------
Use pkgconfig information for cfitsio if available.


3. Application module
---------------------


4. FITS I/O Interface
---------------------
Pass GFitsHDU as reference in GFits::append() method. GFits now properly
deallocates all HDUs on file closing and instance destruction. This
fixes a memory leak that occured in earlier version.


5. Linear algebra module
------------------------
None


6. Model module
---------------
None


7. Numerics module
------------------
None


8. Observation module
---------------------
GObservations now correctly clones observation in copy operations and
deallocates all obserations on destruction. This fixes memory leaks that
were introduced by using the std::vector template class to hold observations.


9. Optimization module
----------------------
None


10. Sky module
--------------
None


11. Support module
------------------
None


12. XML module
--------------
GXmlElement now correctly clones attributes in copy operations and
deallocates all attributes on destruction. GXmlNode now correctly clones
nodes in copy operations and deallocates all nodes on destruction.
This fixes memory leaks that were introduced by using the std::vector
template class to hold attributes and nodes.



13. Multi-wavelength interface
------------------------------
None


14. Fermi-LAT interface
----------------------
None


15. CTA interface
-----------------
Implement improved integration scheme for extended source (now operates
in reference frame of model).

